#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Bhāravagga "
msgstr "3. The Burden "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Bhārasutta "
msgstr "22. The Burden "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.22:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ … tatra kho … "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.22:1.2"
msgid "“bhārañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi bhārahārañca bhārādānañca bhāranikkhepanañca. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the burden, the bearer of the burden, the picking up of the burden, and the putting down of the burden. "

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.22:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhāro? "
msgstr "And what is the burden? "

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.5"
msgid "Pañcupādānakkhandhā tissa vacanīyaṃ. "
msgstr "The five grasping aggregates, it should be said. "

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.6"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.7"
msgid "Rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho; "
msgstr "The grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.8"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāro. "
msgstr "This is called the burden. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.22:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhārahāro? "
msgstr "And who is the bearer of the burden? "

msgctxt "sn22.22:2.2"
msgid "Puggalo tissa vacanīyaṃ. "
msgstr "The person, it should be said; "

msgctxt "sn22.22:2.3"
msgid "Yvāyaṃ āyasmā evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto; "
msgstr "the venerable of such and such name and clan. "

msgctxt "sn22.22:2.4"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhārahāro. "
msgstr "This is called the bearer of the burden. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.26, sc3
msgctxt "sn22.22:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bhārādānaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the picking up of the burden? "

# NOTE: As usual, I prefer to translate tatra tatra and related idioms as distributive.
#. VAR: ponobhavikā → ponobbhavikā (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: nandīrāgasahagatā → nandirāgasahagatā (sabbattha)
msgctxt "sn22.22:3.2"
msgid "Yāyaṃ taṇhā ponobhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It’s the craving that leads to future lives, mixed up with relishing and greed, taking pleasure in various different realms. That is, "

msgctxt "sn22.22:3.3"
msgid "kāmataṇhā, bhavataṇhā, vibhavataṇhā. "
msgstr "craving for sensual pleasures, craving to continue existence, and craving to end existence. "

msgctxt "sn22.22:3.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhārādānaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the picking up of the burden. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn22.22:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bhāranikkhepanaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the putting down of the burden? "

msgctxt "sn22.22:4.2"
msgid "Yo tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo. "
msgstr "It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not adhering to it. "

msgctxt "sn22.22:4.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāranikkhepanan”ti. "
msgstr "This is called the putting down of the burden.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.22:5.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

#. VAR: vatvāna → vatvā (bj)
msgctxt "sn22.22:5.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.1"
msgid "“Bhārā have pañcakkhandhā, "
msgstr "“The five aggregates are indeed burdens, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.2"
msgid "bhārahāro ca puggalo; "
msgstr "and the person is the bearer of the burden. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.3"
msgid "Bhārādānaṃ dukhaṃ loke, "
msgstr "Picking up the burden is suffering in the world, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.4"
msgid "bhāranikkhepanaṃ sukhaṃ. "
msgstr "and putting the burden down is happiness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.1"
msgid "Nikkhipitvā garuṃ bhāraṃ, "
msgstr "When the heavy burden is put down "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.2"
msgid "aññaṃ bhāraṃ anādiya; "
msgstr "without picking up another, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: taṇhamabbuyha → taṇhaṃ abbuyha (bj, s1-3) | taṇhamabbhuyha (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.3"
msgid "Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha, "
msgstr "and craving’s pulled out from the root, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.4"
msgid "nicchāto parinibbuto”ti. "
msgstr "you’re hungerless, extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
